docs.abstract: In a wide-ranging career, he designed cars, restaurants and, most notably, the otherworldly look of science-fiction movies.
docs.snippet: In a wide-ranging career, he designed cars, restaurants and, most notably, the otherworldly look of science-fiction movies.
docs.lead_paragraph: Syd Mead, a designer whose wide-ranging work included envisioning vehicles of the future as well as helping to shape the look of environments in movies like “Blade Runner,” “Tron” and “Aliens,” died on Monday at his home in Pasadena, Calif. He was 86.

headline.main: Syd Mead, 86, Maker of Future Worlds in ‘Blade Runner’ and More, Dies
headline.print_headline: Syd Mead, Who Envisioned the Future and Then Designed It, Is Dead at 86

docs.abstract: Venezuela’s government opposes the Rev. Nelson Sandoval and some in his neglected Indigenous village see him as a know-it-all, but to many, he’s a lifeline.
docs.snippet: Venezuela’s government opposes the Rev. Nelson Sandoval and some in his neglected Indigenous village see him as a know-it-all, but to many, he’s a lifeline.
docs.lead_paragraph: EL TUKUKO, Venezuela — The Rev. Nelson Sandoval’s repeated clashes with Socialist officials, Marxist rebels and tribal chiefs have earned him both loyal followers and bitter enemies in a remote and neglected Indigenous village in the rainforest of western Venezuela.

headline.main: Do-gooder or ‘Devil’? A Friar’s Work Divides a Venezuelan Village

docs.abstract: The 16th arrondissement is turning into a dining destination. François-Régis Gaudry, the popular food writer and radio host, offers compelling reasons to eat in the neighborhood.
docs.snippet: The 16th arrondissement is turning into a dining destination. François-Régis Gaudry, the popular food writer and radio host, offers compelling reasons to eat in the neighborhood.
docs.lead_paragraph: Among the most dense and affluent districts in Paris, the 16th arrondissement has long been considered a sleepy, stuffy, gastronomic desert on the French capital’s vast culinary landscape. François-Régis Gaudry, the 44-year-old food critic, radio and television host, and best-selling author of Let’s Eat France!, knows the area’s limitations firsthand: Every week for the last decade, he has recorded his wildly popular radio show, “On Va Déguster,” at La Maison de la Radio, the 16th arrondissement headquarters for Radio France broadcasting. But now there are compelling reasons to direct appetites here on the city’s western edge.

headline.main: Five Places to Dine in Paris With the Author of ‘Let’s Eat France’
headline.print_headline: A Compelling Argument for the 16th Arrondissement
